# 🌌 Imagine Mode Guide

**Mode:** `Imagine`
**Purpose:** Concept exploration — generate high-impact visual ideas from scratch using just a prompt, without requiring modeling or setup.  

---

## 🎯 Overview

Imagine Mode in KeyShot AI is built for **early-stage creative thinking** — a freeform visual canvas driven entirely by text. It lets users quickly generate evocative concept visuals to explore **form, setting, mood, and visual direction**, without the need to model anything upfront.

This is the go-to mode for creating **moodboards**, pitching **visual territories**, and kickstarting projects with **imagination-first storytelling**.

---

## 🧠 Key Behavior

* Users provide prompts describing abstract concepts, moods, or environments.
* AI generates complete visual outputs — no model or setup needed.
* Perfect for raw inspiration, team alignment, or speculative directions.
* No expectations of realism or product accuracy — just storytelling and mood.

---

🌌 Imagine Mode for Texture & Gobo Generation
Use Case: Create stylized concept images to be used as custom gobo cutouts, projection masks, or texture overlays — especially black & white or silhouette-based.

🎯 Creative Guidelines
✅ What works well:

High-contrast black-and-white scenes

Isolated silhouettes or symbolic shapes

Atmospheric lightplay (e.g., shadows, mist, glow edges)

Abstract organic or architectural forms

🚫 What to avoid:

Real-world logos, branded designs

Over-detailed scenes (should stay iconic/symbolic)

Mentions of camera, UVs, renders, or geometry structure

🔧 New Prompt Template: Textural/Lighting Asset Concept
Imagine a [black and white / high-contrast / minimal] visual of [subject], designed as a [texture, projection, or gobo image]. The composition should be clean and iconic, with [lighting or form cues]. This will support material exploration or lighting design.

✅ Example Prompts for Gobo / Texture Concepts
🌳 Organic Gobo – Nature Theme
“Imagine a black-and-white silhouette of a tree with bare branches and birds perched in delicate poses. The image is clean, iconic, and framed to be used as a gobo light texture — evocative of quiet nature and soft shadow play.”

🏙️ Architectural Pattern for Light Casting
“Imagine a sharp black-and-white pattern of geometric window panes and steel trusses, backlit with directional light casting angled shadows. The result should resemble an abstract urban skyline — perfect for lighting overlays or textural moodboards.”

🌀 Abstract Material Map
“Imagine a high-contrast swirl pattern resembling ink in water, rendered in flowing black and white gradients. The image should feel dynamic and organic, suitable for use as a texture mask in soft-touch polymers or iridescent coatings.”

🧠 Bonus: Suggested Subject Themes
