## 🔧 Qwen-Optimized Structured Prompts for Imagine

As of KeyShot 2026.1, the Qwen model benefits from structured, attribute-based prompts even for abstract concept generation. For Imagine Mode, all fields are active since the entire scene is generated from scratch.

### Full Structured Imagine Template

```
SUBJECT: [primary scene element or concept]
ATTRIBUTES: [form, design language, distinguishing visual traits]
STATE: [condition, atmosphere, temporal cue]
COMPOSITION: [framing, angle, depth staging]
ENVIRONMENT: [setting, spatial context, world type]
LIGHTING: [source, direction, softness, color temperature, mood]
MATERIALS: [surface types, textures, reflectivity, micro-detail]
COLOR: [dominant palette, accents, saturation, contrast]
CAMERA: [lens feel, depth of field, perspective]
STYLE: [visual medium, genre, aesthetic treatment]
QUALITY: [detail level, realism target, atmosphere]
EXCLUSIONS: [unwanted elements, artifact suppression]
```

### Example: Bio-Tech Concept Scene

**Structured:**
```
SUBJECT: organic translucent growth structure
ATTRIBUTES: flowing biomorphic forms, bioluminescent veins, coral-like branching
STATE: slowly pulsing with internal light, alive and growing
COMPOSITION: wide establishing shot, subject centered with depth layers
ENVIRONMENT: underwater cavern with soft volumetric haze
LIGHTING: bioluminescent internal glow, soft teal ambient fill, subtle caustic patterns
MATERIALS: translucent organic membrane, iridescent chitinous shell, wet glossy surfaces
COLOR: deep ocean teal, bioluminescent cyan, warm amber glow accents
CAMERA: 24mm wide-angle feel, moderate depth of field, immersive perspective
STYLE: cinematic concept art with grounded bio-organic realism
QUALITY: high detail, atmospheric depth, rich volumetric lighting
EXCLUSIONS: no people, no mechanical elements, no text, no branded content
```

